..TEXT:
`He loved also in life," says Arrivabene,
^Commento Storico~, 584, "a certain Belacqua, an excellent maker
of musical instruments."
..TEXT:
Benvenuto da Imola says of him:
..TEXT:
<<<FORMATTING-OFF>>>
     "He was a Florentine who made guitars and other musical
     instruments.  He carved and ornamented the necks and head of
     the guitars with great care, and sometimes also played.
     Hence Dante, who delighted in music, knew him intimately."
     This seems to be all that is known of Belacqua.
..TCHR:
